NAME
	llm-sessions (display) - render a multi-track timeline of vertical bars positioned by sample timestamp and scaled by token count

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	sessions	one numeric session id per line
	<id>/history	lines "ms tokens limit", oldest first

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	Each session id becomes a horizontal track; each history sample a
	vertical bar placed on a shared time axis spanning the min..max
	timestamp across all tracks, scaled against the global limit
	maximum.  Keeps no local state - the recorder owns the ring.
	No pointer or key handling.

SEE ALSO
	llm-recorder (produces this input tree)
